# Chishma, Uguzevsky Selsoviet, Birsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Chishma (; , Şişmä) is a rural locality (a village) in Uguzevsky Selsoviet, Birsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 24 as of 2010.
Geography
It is located 23&nbsp;km from Birsk and 2&nbsp;km from Uguzevo.
